# 4. Sliding Window Maximum ⭐

Very famous interview question.

Given:

```text id="j4z7v3"
window size k
```

Return:

```text id="x1m9r5"
maximum element in every window
```

Example:

```text id="v6n4b2"
[1,3,-1,-3,5,3,6,7]
k = 3

Output:
[3,3,5,5,6,7]
```

---

# Core Idea

Deque maintains elements in:

```text id="u9f2k1"
decreasing order
```

Front always contains maximum.

---

# Why This Problem Is Important

It teaches:

* monotonic deque
* removing smaller useless elements
* O(n) optimization

This is a VERY important interview pattern.

---

# 5. Sliding Window Minimum

Same as maximum.

But deque maintained in:

```text id="v0m5z8"
increasing order
```

